      • withMavenVersions

        public SingleBracketPomTokenParserFactory.Builder withMavenVersions(String reactorPomMavenVersion,
                                                                    String topParentMavenVersion)
        Assigns the two Maven versions used to create POM Tokens within this Builder. For PomType.REACTOR and PomType.ROOT_REACTOR projects, the reactorPomMavenVersion is used, and for other projects the topParentMavenVersion version is used. This BuilderStep provides the possibility to use different Maven versions for the parent POM and the current POM, which is required in root/top reactor and root/top parent poms. For example, a typical tokenization for a root reactor template POM uses the following structure: 
             
             <parent>
                 <groupId>[parentGroupId]</groupId>
                 <artifactId>[parentArtifactId]</artifactId>
                 <version>[project:reactorParent.mavenVersion]</version>
                 <relativePath>[parentPomRelativePath]</relativePath>
             </parent>


             <groupId>[groupId]</groupId>
             <artifactId>[artifactId]</artifactId>
             <version>[mavenVersion]</version>
        Parameters:
        reactorPomMavenVersion - The version of the reactor POMs. Note that this is not identical to project.getReactorParent().getMavenVersion(), since the reactor parent's maven version is the version of the parent element for the root/topmost reactor POM in the project.
        topParentMavenVersion - The version of the
        Returns:
        The next BuilderStep subtype in the builder chain.

      • isProjectNameAddedToDirectories

        protected boolean isProjectNameAddedToDirectories()
        Returns:
        true if this BuilderStep should add prefixes with the Project's name to local project directory names. This means that SoftwareComponent directories should be given names on the form foo-finance-api instead of finance-api, given that the project's name is foo and the SoftwareComponent's finance.

      • tokenize

        protected List<String> tokenize(String path)
        Converts the supplied path to a List of segments, assuming that the path uses '/' chars to separate directory names. Returning a List containing all directory names (i.e. path parts) in their order of occurrence.
        Parameters:
        path - The path to tokenize, assumed to use '/' as separator chars.
        Returns:
        A List whose elements contain the directory names within the supplied path.
